{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/posts/Anemia/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Anemia","time":"January 13, 2021","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.3333333333333333,"src":"/static/cf378f5a7d637be7b68eb716cb91a866/2f1b1/cover.jpg","srcSet":"/static/cf378f5a7d637be7b68eb716cb91a866/fd013/cover.jpg 200w,\n/static/cf378f5a7d637be7b68eb716cb91a866/25252/cover.jpg 400w,\n/static/cf378f5a7d637be7b68eb716cb91a866/2f1b1/cover.jpg 800w,\n/static/cf378f5a7d637be7b68eb716cb91a866/0ff54/cover.jpg 1200w,\n/static/cf378f5a7d637be7b68eb716cb91a866/06655/cover.jpg 1600w,\n/static/cf378f5a7d637be7b68eb716cb91a866/097fa/cover.jpg 1920w","srcWebp":"/static/cf378f5a7d637be7b68eb716cb91a866/ccdb5/cover.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/cf378f5a7d637be7b68eb716cb91a866/6b183/cover.webp 200w,\n/static/cf378f5a7d637be7b68eb716cb91a866/fc32b/cover.webp 400w,\n/static/cf378f5a7d637be7b68eb716cb91a866/ccdb5/cover.webp 800w,\n/static/cf378f5a7d637be7b68eb716cb91a866/9000d/cover.webp 1200w,\n/static/cf378f5a7d637be7b68eb716cb91a866/e0075/cover.webp 1600w,\n/static/cf378f5a7d637be7b68eb716cb91a866/30cf3/cover.webp 1920w","sizes":"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px"}}},"tags":["Medicine","Hematopoietic"]},"wordCount":{"words":391},"timeToRead":2,"html":"<h2>Anemia is not having enough RBCs to deliver O2.</h2>\n<p>RBCs come from HSCs.\nMany chemicals control HSC to RBC differentiation.\nAnd EPO, made in the kidneys, is an important stimulator of this.\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 665px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 65.49999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Screen Shot 2021 01 13 at 10 26 06 AM\"\n        title=\"Screen Shot 2021 01 13 at 10 26 06 AM\"\n        src=\"/static/0db41785dcea95ec10592adcf9a4164b/5f4af/Screen%20Shot%202021-01-13%20at%2010.26.06%20AM.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0db41785dcea95ec10592adcf9a4164b/772e8/Screen%20Shot%202021-01-13%20at%2010.26.06%20AM.png 200w,\n/static/0db41785dcea95ec10592adcf9a4164b/e17e5/Screen%20Shot%202021-01-13%20at%2010.26.06%20AM.png 400w,\n/static/0db41785dcea95ec10592adcf9a4164b/5f4af/Screen%20Shot%202021-01-13%20at%2010.26.06%20AM.png 665w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 665px) 100vw, 665px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 660px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 84.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Screen Shot 2021 01 13 at 10 26 23 AM\"\n        title=\"Screen Shot 2021 01 13 at 10 26 23 AM\"\n        src=\"/static/6bc1d7974d915a8d780d4d6dad8d10d3/1f083/Screen%20Shot%202021-01-13%20at%2010.26.23%20AM.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6bc1d7974d915a8d780d4d6dad8d10d3/772e8/Screen%20Shot%202021-01-13%20at%2010.26.23%20AM.png 200w,\n/static/6bc1d7974d915a8d780d4d6dad8d10d3/e17e5/Screen%20Shot%202021-01-13%20at%2010.26.23%20AM.png 400w,\n/static/6bc1d7974d915a8d780d4d6dad8d10d3/1f083/Screen%20Shot%202021-01-13%20at%2010.26.23%20AM.png 660w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 660px) 100vw, 660px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h2>We make a lof of RBCs in various tissues during fetal stage.</h2>\n<p>Fetus makes most of its RBC in the yolk sac in the first few months, then liver, then spleen, and finally marrow in the later months.\nBut after the birth, the newborn starts to breath the air and this results in delivering much more O2 to the body compared to when the newborn was a fetus relying on placenta for O2.\nSo 10 days after the birth, a newborn's RBC production decreases because there is enough O2 being delivered.\nThis is the peak of erythroblast concentration in the marrow.\nThe decrease in erythroblast results in an anemia, whihc we all go through.\nThis physiologic anemia stimulates the kidneys to increase EPO to stimulate more RBC production.\nAs we become adult, we make more RBCs.\nBut we won't be making as much as we were a newborn.\nFinally after 65 years, 1/4 won't be able to make a normal amount of RBCs.</p>\n<h2>Masuring hemoglobin, RBC count, and MCV are helpful in identifying anemia.</h2>\n<p>Measuring hemoglobin identifies its concentration.\nMeasuring RBC count identifies the number of RBCs.\nAnd measuring MCV identifies the size of RBCs.</p>\n<p>But the following conditions make it difficult to assess anemia:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Plasma volume change (can be from dehydration, burn, or pregnancy)</li>\n<li>Increaed O2 demand (can be from decreased O2 loading by the lungs)</li>\n<li>RBC defects</li>\n<li>Hemogrolib defects</li>\n<li>Acute bleeding</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For example, hematocrit can go below the normal range during pregnancy but this is because pregnancy increases the RBCs by 30% but plasma volume by 50%.</p>\n<h2>History and physical exam can help identify anemia.</h2>\n<p>Anemic patients may present with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fever</li>\n<li>Bruise</li>\n<li>Weight loss</li>\n<li>Adenopathy</li>\n<li>Juandice</li>\n<li>Hepatomegaly</li>\n<li>Splenomegaly</li>\n<li>Nail abnormality</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Anemia can be related with other conditions:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cancer</li>\n<li>Blood disease</li>\n<li>Renal disease</li>\n<li>Liver disease</li>\n<li>Infection</li>\n<li>Rheumatoid arthritis</li>\n<li>SLE</li>\n<li>Endocrine disease</li>\n<li>Cardiac disease</li>\n<li>Drugs</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Look at the peripheral blood smear to see RBC abnormality to classify anemia.</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Screen Shot 2021 01 13 at 10 26 36 AM\"\n        title=\"Screen Shot 2021 01 13 at 10 26 36 AM\"\n        src=\"/static/5378523680f9a437ae316b9489cf48a0/5a190/Screen%20Shot%202021-01-13%20at%2010.26.36%20AM.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5378523680f9a437ae316b9489cf48a0/772e8/Screen%20Shot%202021-01-13%20at%2010.26.36%20AM.png 200w,\n/static/5378523680f9a437ae316b9489cf48a0/e17e5/Screen%20Shot%202021-01-13%20at%2010.26.36%20AM.png 400w,\n/static/5378523680f9a437ae316b9489cf48a0/5a190/Screen%20Shot%202021-01-13%20at%2010.26.36%20AM.png 800w,\n/static/5378523680f9a437ae316b9489cf48a0/1b19f/Screen%20Shot%202021-01-13%20at%2010.26.36%20AM.png 991w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span>\nAnemia with normal RBC size is normocytic.\nAnemia with small RBC is microcytic.\nAnd anemia with large RBC is macrocytic.</p>"},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/posts/Hematopoiesis/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Hematopoiesis"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/posts/Headache/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Headache"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"14fd84